.demo-description
  %p    
    We can have a full control on what is done at server side when we save the data.
    It is well known that the post can be successful, but the same saving to the database fails.
    To control that issue we can use a callback function when data is saved to the server.
    The function accepts one parameter - data returned from the server. Depending on this data
    the function should return true or false. When true this means the saving is done and false it failed.
/ End demo-description
